你是保管人
You were the custodian.

174
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:15,320
如果你是开银行的而银行被抢劫了
If you were a bank and were robbed.

175
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:17,400
你不能就告诉储户们顺其自然吧
You could not simply tell your depositors to go hang.

176
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,430
别跟我打比方
I do not entertain hypotheticals.

177
00:10:19,430 --> 00:10:21,460
世道本来就已经很烦人了
The world as it is is vexing enough.

178
00:10:22,620 --> 00:10:25,530
其次  你对马的估价过高了
Secondly your evaluation of the horse is high.

179
00:10:25,530 --> 00:10:27,740
你至少高估了两百块  你多大了
By about two hundred dollars. How old are you?

180
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:29,840
我跟你说  我的估价绝对是低价
If anything, my prices is low.

181
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:32,030
茱迪是一匹优质的赛马种马
My Judy was a fine racing mare.

182
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:33,220
我看到她 
I've seen her

183
00:10:33,230 --> 00:10:34,960
能驮着一个很重的骑手跳过八栅栅栏 
jump a eight-rail fence with a heavy rider.

184
00:10:34,970 --> 00:10:37,870
-我十四岁 -是吗  真有意思
- I am fourteen. - Oh, well, it's all very interesting.

185
00:10:38,530 --> 00:10:41,050
小马驹是你们的了  你得收下
The ponies are yours, take them.

186
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:43,930
你父亲的马是被杀人犯偷走的
Your father horse was stolen by a murderous criminal.

187
00:10:43,930 --> 00:10:46,000
鉴于我们之间的默示协议
I have provided reasonable protection

188
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,640
我已经为它做了足够的保护措施
for the creature as per our implicit agreement.

189
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:51,790
我的马厩管理员牙齿都被打掉了  
My watchmen had his teeth knocked out,

190
00:10:51,790 --> 00:10:53,050
他现在只能喝汤了
and can take only soup.

191
00:10:53,050 --> 00:10:54,520
那我们法庭上见吧
That would take it to law.

192
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:56,010
你没有理由起诉我
You have no case.

193
00:10:56,010 --> 00:10:57,930
阿肯色州洁特律师也许不会同意
Lawyer J. Noble Daggett of Dardanelle, Arkansas may think otherwise.

194
00:10:57,930 --> 00:10:59,760
陪审团估计也不会同意你的观点
As might a jury.

195
00:10:59,770 --> 00:11:01,730
一个寡妇和三个孩子的诉状胜算不会小
Petitioned by a widow and three small children.

196
00:11:04,380 --> 00:11:06,800
我会往你父亲的账户里
I will pay two hundred dollars

197
00:11:06,810 --> 00:11:09,230
打两百美元
to your fathers estate.

198
00:11:09,230 --> 00:11:11,720
前提条件是  我要收到你律师的文件
When I have in my hand a letter from your lawyer,

199
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:15,850
免除我到今天为止的一切责任
absolving me of all liability from the beginning of the world to date.

200
00:11:15,850 --> 00:11:16,930
茱迪的价格是两百块
I'll take two hundred dollars for Judy,

201
00:11:16,930 --> 00:11:18,230
小马驹是一百块
plus one hundred for the ponies.

202
00:11:18,230 --> 00:11:18,850
另有二十五块
And twenty five dollars

203
00:11:18,850 --> 00:11:20,720
是那匹汤姆・切尼留下的灰马
for the grey horse that Tom Chaney left.

204
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:22,450
市场上很容易就能四十块出手的
He was easily worth forty.

205
00:11:22,450 --> 00:11:24,800
那一共是三百二十五块
That is three hundred and twenty-five dollars total.

206
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:28,040
小马驹不算在内  我是不会买的
The ponies have no part in it. I will not buy them.

207
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:30,120
那茱迪的价格就是三百二十五块
Then the price for Judy is three hundred and twenty-five dollars.

208
00:11:30,410 --> 00:11:34,140
就算是飞马我也不会出这么多钱的
I would not pay three hundred and twenty-five dollars for winged Pegasus.

209
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:37,540
还有  那匹灰马根本就不是你的
As for the grey horse, it does not belong to you.

210
00:11:37,540 --> 00:11:39,500
那匹马是我父亲借给汤姆・切尼的
The grey horse was lent to Tom Chaney by my father.

211
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:41,290
切尼只是借用而已
Chaney only had the use of him.

212
00:11:42,790 --> 00:11:45,490
我会付给你二百二十五块
I would pay two hundred and twenty five dollars.

213
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,380
但我要留着那匹灰马
And keep the grey horse.

214
00:11:47,380 --> 00:11:48,870
另外还有小马驹我也收下
And I want the ponies.

215
00:11:48,870 --> 00:11:50,000
我不接受
I cannot accept that.

216
00:11:50,010 --> 00:11:52,690
我离开这里之后就不会有和解了 
There will be no settlement after I leave this office

217
00:11:52,690 --> 00:11:54,580
-我们法庭上见  -好吧  我让步
- and it will go to law. - All right, this is my last offer.

218
00:11:55,420 --> 00:11:57,380
两百五十块
Two hundred and fifty dollars.

219
00:11:57,380 --> 00:12:00,890
前提是我拿到先前说的免责文件
For that I get the release, previously discussed.

220
00:12:00,890 --> 00:12:03,010
还有你父亲的马鞍
And I keep your father's saddle.

221
00:12:03,020 --> 00:12:05,170
灰马不由得你来卖
The grey horse is not yours to sell.

222
00:12:05,170 --> 00:12:07,250
那马鞍是无价的  我要留着它
The saddle is not for sale. I will keep it.

223
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:09,260
洁特律师会证明那匹灰马的归属权
Lawyer Dagget will prove ownership of the grey horse.

224
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:11,360
他会发函向你追缴非法强占财产的
He will come after you with a writ of replevin.

225
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:14,540
什么  好吧  听好了
What? All right, now look, listen very carefully.

226
00:12:14,540 --> 00:12:16,250
我不会再让步了
As I will not bargain further.

227
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:17,960
我要回小马驹
I'll will take the ponies back,

228
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:19,840
那匹灰马本来就是我的
and the grey horse, which is mine.

229
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:21,000
妥协价是...
And settle...

230
00:12:22,220 --> 00:12:25,970
三百美元  就这么说定了
For three hundred dollars. Now you must take that or leave it.

231
00:12:25,970 --> 00:12:28,190
我豁出去了
And I do not much care which it is.

232
00:12:30,740 --> 00:12:32,300
杰特律师是不会让我
Lawyer Daggett would not wish me to

233
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:34,920
接受任何低于三百二十五块的补偿的
consider anything under three hundred and twenty-five dollars.

234
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:37,550
但是我想三百二十块就够了
But I will settle for three hundred and twenty.

235
00:12:37,550 --> 00:12:40,540
如果那二十块是提前支付的话
If I am given twenty in advance.

236
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:42,560
好了  现在我们再说说那个马鞍
Now here's what I have to say about that saddle.

237
00:12:49,860 --> 00:12:52,310
弗兰克・罗斯的女儿吗
Frank Ross's daughter.

238
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:54,800
哦  可怜的孩子
Oh, poor child.

239
00:12:58,540 --> 00:13:00,360
你是准备在这儿呆一阵子
Are you are gonna staying with us,

240
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:02,770
还是你马上就回家看你妈妈呢
or you hurrying back home to your Mama?

241
00:13:02,770 --> 00:13:04,590
我想留在这儿  如果方便的话
I'll stay here, if you can have me.

242
00:13:05,170 --> 00:13:07,430
我昨晚在收敛师那儿过的夜
I just spend last night at the undertakers.

243
00:13:07,430 --> 00:13:09,160
陪着三具尸体
In the company of three corpses.

244
00:13:09,590 --> 00:13:11,220
我觉得我像是以西结
I felt like Ezekiel.

245
00:13:09,590 --> 00:13:13,640
以西结: 希伯来先知
旧约圣经以西结书之作者

246
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:13,640
在死亡谷中
In valley of the dry bones.

247
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:15,250
上帝保佑你
Then, God bless you.

248
00:13:15,550 --> 00:13:19,610
你和祖母特纳睡在一个房间
Now that you'll be rooming with, Grandma Turner.

249
00:13:19,620 --> 00:13:21,210
我们得挤一挤了
We had to double up,

250
00:13:21,210 --> 00:13:24,170
因为许多人都前来看绞刑
what with all the people in town come to see the hanging.

251
00:13:26,220 --> 00:13:29,160
这些是你父亲屋中的遗物
This was in your poor father's room.

252
00:13:29,170 --> 00:13:31,270
这就是所有的东西了
That is everything.

253
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:33,650
这栋房子里没有小偷的
There are no light fingers in this house.

254
00:13:42,270 --> 00:13:45,750
如果你需要什么来装那把枪
If you need something for to tote the gun around?

255
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:49,840
我可以给你一个面粉袋  只要五分钱
I can give you an empty flour sack for a nickel.

256
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,750
他在那儿发现了什么
...about what he found up here,

257
00:14:22,750 --> 00:14:25,840
我们离波特警官很近
and we're close enough to deputy Marshal Potter

258
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:28,840
所以我们就靠近那里去调查了
that we thought we'd better ride over ourselves and investigate.

259
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:30,990
那么你看到什么了
And what did you see when you arrived?

260
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:35,240
一个女人  在院子那里
A woman, was out in the yard.

261
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:37,780
她死了  脸上都是苍蝇
Dead with blow flies on her face.

262
00:14:38,230 --> 00:14:40,020
一个老人在院子里面 
The old man was inside

263
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:42,530
他的胸脯被霰弹枪打开花了  
with his breast opened by a scatter-gun

264
00:14:42,530 --> 00:14:43,790
他的脚被烧焦了
and his feet burned.

265
00:14:44,060 --> 00:14:45,700
他那时候还活着  但也只剩一口气了
He was still alive, but just was.

266
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:47,960
他说是沃顿兄弟俩干的
Said it was them two Wharton boys had done it.

267
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:49,920
-他们聚在一起  喝醉了  -反对
- Rode up, drunk. - Objection.

268
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:51,200
道听途说
Hearsay.

269
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:53,640
那可是临终遗言  法官大人
Dying declaration, your honor.

270
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:55,820
反对无效  请继续  考伯恩先生
Objection's overruled. Proceed Mr. Cogburn.

271
00:14:55,820 --> 00:15:00,820
然后兄弟二人  奥多斯和赛思将他推倒在地
Them two Wharton boys, Odus and C.C. throwed down on him,

272
00:15:01,110 --> 00:15:04,450
问他钱在哪儿  但是他没说
and asked him where his money was, but he wouldn't tell them.

273
00:15:04,450 --> 00:15:07,130
他们在他脚上抹上松子油  点火拷问他
They lit pine nut held them to his feet.

274
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:10,910
他说钱在一个水果罐头中
He told them the money was in the fruit jar.

275
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:14,250
在烟熏屋旁的一块灰色岩石下面
Under a grey rock at the corner of the smoke house.

276
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:15,260
然后呢
And then?

277
00:15:15,810 --> 00:15:19,390
他死了  死时相当痛苦
Well he died on us, Passed away in considerable pain.

278
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:20,450
然后你做了什么
What'd you do then?

279
00:15:20,910 --> 00:15:23,530
我和波特警官找到烟熏屋
I made Marshal Potter and went out to the smoke house

280
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:25,430
发现那块岩石被搬走了
and that rock had been moved,

281
00:15:25,430 --> 00:15:27,770
然后那罐钱也不见了
the jar with the money in it was gone.

282
00:15:27,770 --> 00:15:30,610
-反对  纯属猜测  -反对有效
-Objection, speculative. -Sustained.

283
00:15:30,610 --> 00:15:34,220
你们在烟熏屋旁边找到了那个灰岩石
You found a flat grey rock, in the corner of the smoke house.

284
00:15:34,220 --> 00:15:36,530
下面有个洞
With a hollowed out space beneth it.

285
00:15:36,540 --> 00:15:38,190
如果被告要陈述证据
If the prosecutor is going to give evidence,

286
00:15:38,190 --> 00:15:39,840
我希望他能宣誓
I suggest he be sworn.

287
00:15:40,790 --> 00:15:42,120
考伯恩先生  你在烟熏屋附近
Mr. Cogburn. What did you find,

288
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:44,100
找到了什么东西
if anything, in the corner of that smokehouse?

289
00:15:44,330 --> 00:15:45,780
有一块平整的灰色岩石
We found a flat gray rock with

290
00:15:45,780 --> 00:15:48,380
下面有个洞  里面什么都没有
a hollowed-out space under it. Nothing there.

291
00:15:48,380 --> 00:15:50,470
-然后呢  -没有罐子  什么也没有
- Well then what did you...? - No jar or nothing.

292
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,410
那之后你做什么了吗
Well, what did you do then?

293
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:54,120
然后  我去到沃顿兄弟那里
Well, rode up to the Wharton boys there,

294
00:15:54,130 --> 00:15:56,640
离北福克河与加拿大河的汇流处不远
near where the North Fork strikes the Canadian.

295
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:58,890
-..加拿大河支流  -你发现了什么
- ...branch of the Canadian. - What did you find?

296
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:03,900
我用望远镜看到兄弟俩和他们的父亲艾伦
I had my glass and we spotted the two boys and their old daddy Aaron.

297
00:16:04,450 --> 00:16:06,680
他们和一些畜养猪在溪流岸边
down on the creek bank with some hogs.

298
00:16:07,340 --> 00:16:08,740
他们杀了一头小猪
They'd killed a shoat.

299
00:16:08,740 --> 00:16:11,810
然后便生火烧水
And a fire built up under a wash pot for scalding water.

300
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:12,760
之后你做了什么
What did you do?

301
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:16,080
我对着艾伦喊  我们是美国法警
Announced we was U.S. Marshals, I hollered out to Aaron.

302
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:18,500
我要和他儿子们谈谈
I needed to talk to his two boys.

303
00:16:19,330 --> 00:16:21,030
他抡起斧子
He raised an axe,

304
00:16:21,030 --> 00:16:23,850
开始咒骂我们  并且侮辱法庭公正
and commence to cussing us and blackguarding this court.

305
00:16:23,850 --> 00:16:25,040
那之后呢
What did he do then?

306
00:16:25,690 --> 00:16:28,220
我后退几步  躲开斧子
I backed away from the axe.

307
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:29,960
试着和他讲点道理
Tried to talked some sense into him.

308
00:16:31,810 --> 00:16:33,550
就在这个时候
While this was going on,

309
00:16:33,550 --> 00:16:36,910
赛思躲在升起的蒸汽后面
C.C. edges over to the wash pot there, behind the steam.

310
00:16:37,330 --> 00:16:38,920
拿起一把双管猎枪
And picks up a shot gun.

311
00:16:39,810 --> 00:16:42,160
波特看到了  但是一切都太迟了
Potter seen him, but it was too late.

312
00:16:42,790 --> 00:16:46,100
赛思对着波特开火了
C.C. Wharton pulled out on Potter with one barrel.

313
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:48,430
然后想要打我  我就开枪了
Turned to do the same for me and I shot him.

314
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:51,980
他父亲也抡起了斧子
And the old man raised the axe.

315
00:16:52,030 --> 00:16:53,170
我开枪打了他
And I shot him.

316
00:16:54,350 --> 00:16:56,430
奥多斯想要逃跑  我也对他开了一枪
Odus lit out, and I shot him.

317
00:17:00,980 --> 00:17:04,170
赛思和他老爸倒地后就断气了
C.C. Wharton and Aaron Wharton were dead when they hit the ground,

318
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:05,890
而奥多斯只是被击伤了
Odus was just winged.

319
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:08,770
那你发现装着一百二十美元的罐子了吗
Did you find the jar with a hundred and twenty dollars in it?

320
00:17:08,770 --> 00:17:09,860
-反对  暗示性问题  -反对有效
- Leading. - Sustained.

321
00:17:10,510 --> 00:17:11,840
之后发生了什么
What happened then?

322
00:17:12,050 --> 00:17:14,600
的确找到了里面有一百二十块钱的罐子
Found a jar with a hundred and twenty dollars in it.

323
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:17,710
奥多斯后来怎样了
What became of Odus Wharton?

324
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:19,200
他在那儿坐着呢
There he sits.

325
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:23,200
您可以提问了  高迪先生
You may ask, Mr. Goudy.

326
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,910
谢谢  巴罗先生
Thank you Mr. Barlow.

327
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:40,270
考伯恩先生
Mr. Cogburn.

328
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:43,710
在你担任美国法警职务的四年中
In your four years as a U.S. Marshal.

329
00:17:43,860 --> 00:17:45,590
你对多少人开了枪
How many men have you shot?

330
00:17:47,090 --> 00:17:48,650
我从不无缘无故开枪打人
Never shot nobody that didn't ask for it.

331
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:50,570
你并没有回答我的问题
Well that was not the question.

332
00:17:51,450 --> 00:17:52,510
多少个
How many?

333
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,100
开枪打的还是射杀的
Shot or killed?

334
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:57,040
咱们就限定在你射杀的吧
Let us restrict it to killed

335
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:59,360
这样数目不至于大得说不清
So that we may have a manageable figure.

336
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:00,840
大概十二个
About twelve.

337
00:18:00,850 --> 00:18:05,410
或者十五个  制止斗殴  自卫反击之类的
Fifteen. Stopping men in flight, defending myself, et cetera.

338
00:18:05,410 --> 00:18:07,170
他说大概十二个
Around twelve he says.

339
00:18:07,170 --> 00:18:08,880
或者十五个
Or fifteen.

340
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:12,600
那么多  你甚至都没法给出准确的数字
So many, you cannot keep a precise count.

341
