这儿只有一两条路好走
They couldn't be going but one or two ways.

855
00:45:15,840 --> 00:45:18,730
一条是朝着旋梯山朝北走
Heading north, towards the Winding Stair Mountains.

856
00:45:19,010 --> 00:45:20,560
另外一条就是朝西走
Pushing further west.

857
00:45:21,740 --> 00:45:23,540
我猜是北边  那容易抢到东西
I suspect north. There is more to rob.

858
00:45:24,090 --> 00:45:25,430
我买了家餐馆
I bought an eating place.

859
00:45:25,440 --> 00:45:26,680
起名叫"绿蛙"
Called the "Green frog".

860
00:45:26,970 --> 00:45:29,340
从此我自称伯勒先生
Started calling myself, Burroughs.

861
00:45:29,450 --> 00:45:31,690
但我又开始酗酒了
But my drinking picked up.

862
00:45:31,700 --> 00:45:35,440
妻子不喜欢我的那帮狐朋酒友
My wife did not care for the company of my river friends.

863
00:45:35,440 --> 00:45:38,290
她决定重投前夫的怀抱
She decided to go back to her fist husband,

864
00:45:38,290 --> 00:45:40,350
一个五金店的店员
a clerk in a hardware store.

865
00:45:41,230 --> 00:45:43,820
临走前  她和我说  "再见  鲁本"
That was when she said, "Goodbye Reuben."

866
00:45:44,500 --> 00:45:47,420
"你不够得体"
"A love for decency does not abide in you."

867
00:45:47,420 --> 00:45:51,330
一个离婚女人竟和你谈体面
There is a divorced woman talking about decency.

868
00:45:51,330 --> 00:45:53,880
我告诉她   "再见  诺拉"
I told her, "goodbye Nola."

869
00:45:53,880 --> 00:45:57,280
"但愿那卖钉子的混蛋这次能令你快乐"
"I hope that little nail-selling bastard will make you happy this time."

870
00:45:57,280 --> 00:45:59,890
她把我的儿子也带走了
She took my boy with her too.

871
00:46:00,890 --> 00:46:03,370
反正他也不喜欢我
He never cared for me anyway.

872
00:46:04,630 --> 00:46:07,190
估计是对他太凶了
I guess I did speak awful rough to him.

873
00:46:08,170 --> 00:46:10,090
虽然我不是故意的
I did not mean anything by it.

874
00:46:10,940 --> 00:46:13,770
谁都不想有比我儿子贺拉斯还笨的小孩吧
You would not want to see a clumsier child than Horace.

875
00:46:15,720 --> 00:46:18,000
他至少打破了四十个杯子
I bet he broke forty cups...

876
00:46:46,700 --> 00:46:48,030
那是切尼吗
Is it Chaney?

877
00:46:48,830 --> 00:46:51,220
单从脚底  可认不出
I would not recognize the soles of his feet.

878
00:46:51,540 --> 00:46:54,880
那你爬上去看看
Well, you'll have to clamber up and look.

879
00:46:55,760 --> 00:46:57,340
我太老太胖了
I'm too old and too fat.

880
00:46:57,900 --> 00:47:00,910
现在绿蛙那多了张桌球台
Now the Green Frog had one billiard table.

881
00:47:01,280 --> 00:47:04,880
男女都能玩  不过一般都是男的在玩
Served ladies and men both, mostly men.

882
00:47:05,010 --> 00:47:07,380
我曾经想自己经营
I tried to run it myself a while,

883
00:47:07,380 --> 00:47:09,350
但是总是照料不好
but I couldn’t keep good help.

884
00:47:09,770 --> 00:47:12,060
我一直没有学会如何买肉
And I never did learn how to buy meat.

885
00:47:13,240 --> 00:47:14,410
是他吗
Is that him?

886
00:47:15,320 --> 00:47:16,420
我觉得不是
I believe not.

887
00:47:16,420 --> 00:47:18,120
把他放下来
Well, cut him down.

888
00:47:18,460 --> 00:47:19,510
为什么
Why?

889
00:47:19,990 --> 00:47:21,190
我可能认识
I might know him.

890
00:47:25,050 --> 00:47:27,650
所以我就跑去了德州那火烤之地
That was when I went out to the staked plain of Texas,

891
00:47:28,230 --> 00:47:31,050
和弗农・沙夫特  还有个叫奥利的
and shot buffalo with Vernon Shaftoe

892
00:47:31,060 --> 00:47:32,710
平头族印第安人一起猎水牛
and a Flathead Indian named Olly.

893
00:47:33,100 --> 00:47:34,690
摩门一家
The Mormons...

894
00:47:34,690 --> 00:47:37,240
把沙夫特赶出了盐湖城
had run Shaftoe out of Great Salt Lake City,

895
00:47:37,250 --> 00:47:38,700
别问我为什么
but don't ask me what it was for.

896
00:47:38,710 --> 00:47:41,170
就当做误会好了
Call it a misunderstanding and let it go at that.

897
00:47:43,820 --> 00:47:46,890
那些无赖
Well,  the big shaggies,

898
00:47:46,900 --> 00:47:48,540
都散了
about all gone now.

899
00:47:48,540 --> 00:47:49,560
真他妈的遗憾
Damned shame.

900
00:47:51,000 --> 00:47:54,490
现在能买到腌牛舌的话  三美金我也愿意
Give three dollars right now for a pickled buffalo tongue.

901
00:47:57,740 --> 00:47:59,380
为什么要把他吊这么高
Why did they hang him so high?

902
00:47:59,620 --> 00:48:01,280
不知道
I don't know.

903
00:48:01,840 --> 00:48:04,620
可能认为这样可以让他死得更惨
Possibly in the belief it would make him more dead.

904
00:48:18,470 --> 00:48:20,240
我不认识这人
I do not know this man.

905
00:48:51,580 --> 00:48:52,820
你吊死的吗
You hanged him?

906
00:49:00,010 --> 00:49:01,860
为什么他把这吊死的人带走
Why is he taking the hanged man?

907
00:49:01,860 --> 00:49:03,370
他认识的人吗
Did he know him?

908
00:49:03,370 --> 00:49:04,880
不认识
He did not.

909
00:49:05,900 --> 00:49:07,500
好歹是具尸体
But it is a dead body.

910
00:49:07,820 --> 00:49:10,110
可以卖点钱
Must be worth something in the trade.

911
00:49:10,840 --> 00:49:12,930
再说说我第二任妻子  埃德娜
Now my second wife, Edna.

912
00:49:12,930 --> 00:49:15,430
她一直希望我成为律师
She had taken a notion she wanted me to be a lawyer.

913
00:49:15,730 --> 00:49:19,230
买了本很厚的《丹尼尔协商技巧》
Bought this heavy book called Daniel's on Negotiable Instruments.

914
00:49:19,230 --> 00:49:20,930
让我读
Set to make me reading it.

915
00:49:20,930 --> 00:49:24,160
我从来没看懂过
Never could get a grip on it.

916
00:49:24,160 --> 00:49:27,370
我很开心能够撇开它  离开德州
I was happy enough to set it aside and leave Texas.

917
00:49:28,290 --> 00:49:30,880
我们离加拿大不远了
There ain’t six trees between here and Canada,

918
00:49:30,880 --> 00:49:33,310
这段距离几乎寸草不生
nothing else grows but has stickers on it.

919
00:49:33,830 --> 00:49:35,370
问他们...
Ask them...

920
00:49:37,680 --> 00:49:39,800
-我就知道  -知道什么
- I knew it. - Knew what?

921
00:49:40,210 --> 00:49:41,490
有人跟踪我们
We're being followed.

922
00:49:42,390 --> 00:49:44,560
我刚嘱咐那印第安人若发现有人跟着我们
I asked that Indian to signal with a shot

923
00:49:44,570 --> 00:49:46,080
就鸣枪做信号
if someone was on our trail.

924
00:49:47,940 --> 00:49:49,670
我们应该担心吗  警官
Should we be concerned, Marshal?

925
00:49:49,670 --> 00:49:53,770
不用  勒波义夫故意打草惊蛇
No, Mr. LeBoeuf is giving us his bird dog.

926
00:49:53,770 --> 00:49:56,330
一旦计谋成功  他就会飞奔而至
He wants to cut it in, once it flushed his prey.

927
00:49:58,340 --> 00:50:00,940
或许我们可以来回行走
Perhaps we could double back over our tracks,

928
00:50:00,950 --> 00:50:02,320
来混淆他们的追踪
and confuse the trail in a clever way.

929
00:50:02,320 --> 00:50:05,140
不用  我们就在这儿等
No, we will wait right here.

930
00:50:06,300 --> 00:50:08,680
跟我们的朋友问声好
Offer our friend a warm hello.

931
00:50:08,680 --> 00:50:10,600
问问他要去哪儿
Ask him where he's going.

932
00:51:06,500 --> 00:51:08,000
你不是勒波义夫
You are not LeBoeuf.

933
00:51:09,630 --> 00:51:12,030
我叫福斯特
My name is Forster.

934
00:51:12,790 --> 00:51:16,680
我是这里的牙医
I practice dentistry in the nation.

935
00:51:16,680 --> 00:51:18,550
也是兽医
Also, veterinary arts.

936
00:51:18,550 --> 00:51:20,720
也开刀
And medicine,

937
00:51:20,720 --> 00:51:24,390
不过是在那些不会乱动的人们身上
on those humans that will sit still for it.

938
00:51:25,020 --> 00:51:27,750
看来你今天有收获啊
You have your work cut out for you there.

939
00:51:29,760 --> 00:51:34,760
和一个诚恳的印第安人交易的
Traded for him with an Indian, who said he came by him honestly.

940
00:51:35,530 --> 00:51:40,530
我以两面牙医镜一瓶祛痰剂作为交换
I gave up two dental mirrors and a bottle of expectorant.

941
00:51:43,070 --> 00:51:45,360
你们有需要
Do either of you need

942
00:51:45,370 --> 00:51:47,060
医疗救助吗
Medical attention?

943
00:51:47,070 --> 00:51:51,470
没有  要开始变冷了
No. Hey! Fixing to get cold.

944
00:51:51,470 --> 00:51:53,680
你知道哪儿可以避寒吗
Do you know of anywhere to take shelter?

945
00:51:54,170 --> 00:51:56,460
我有熊皮保暖
I have my bearskin.

946
00:52:01,410 --> 00:52:05,570
你可能想去小流氓博本那儿
You might want to head over to the Original Greaser Bob's.

947
00:52:06,290 --> 00:52:11,290
他在卡里伦河那凿了个洞
He notched a dugout into a hollow along the Carrillon River.

948
00:52:12,070 --> 00:52:15,020
你穿过河
If you ride the river,

949
00:52:15,020 --> 00:52:17,100
就能看到了
you won't fail to see it.

950
00:52:17,100 --> 00:52:19,950
小流氓博本创意旅馆
Greaser Bob's, the original.

951
00:52:19,950 --> 00:52:21,570
小流氓博本
Greaser Bob...

952
00:52:21,570 --> 00:52:24,340
在纠察线北边打猎
...is hunting north of the picket wire.

953
00:52:25,030 --> 00:52:28,360
不会在意你借用一下的
And would not begrudge its use.

954
00:52:28,980 --> 00:52:32,630
-多谢  -我已经拔了他的牙齿
- Much obliged. - Now, I have taken his teeth.

955
00:52:33,770 --> 00:52:36,650
我会付价钱
I will entertain an offer,

956
00:52:36,650 --> 00:52:38,350
买下他的其他部分
for the rest of him.

957
00:52:46,940 --> 00:52:48,430
拿着我的大衣
Take my jacket.

958
00:52:49,880 --> 00:52:51,530
轻轻地走到屋顶上
Creep onto the roof.

959
00:52:53,190 --> 00:52:56,350
若他们不友好  听我指令  弄灭烟囱
If they're unfriendly I'll give you a sign to damp the chimney.

960
00:53:21,070 --> 00:53:22,740
谁在外面
Who is out there?

961
00:53:23,230 --> 00:53:24,870
我们想避下寒
We're looking for shelter.

962
00:53:25,670 --> 00:53:28,760
没地方了  快滚
No room for you here! Ride on!

963
00:53:30,550 --> 00:53:31,860
里面都有谁
Who all is in there?

964
00:53:31,860 --> 00:53:32,860
滚
Ride on!

965
00:54:13,690 --> 00:54:15,250
我是联邦官员
I'm a Federal officer.

966
00:54:15,250 --> 00:54:16,330
里面有谁在
Who's in there?

967
00:54:17,880 --> 00:54:19,120
一个圣公会教徒和一个废物
A Methodist and a son of a bitch.

968
00:54:19,470 --> 00:54:21,150
我是大公鸡考伯恩
This is Rooster Cogburn.

969
00:54:21,670 --> 00:54:25,240
还有哥伦布・波特和五名法警
Columbus Potter and five other Marshals is out here with me.

970
00:54:25,690 --> 00:54:27,910
我们有一桶煤油
We have got a bucket of coal oil.

971
00:54:27,910 --> 00:54:30,630
再过一分钟  就点燃你们的房子
In one minute we will burn your house from both ends.

972
00:54:30,630 --> 00:54:32,270
你们一共就两个人
There's only two of you.

973
00:54:32,400 --> 00:54:34,590
有种你就试试看
Go ahead and bet your life on it.

974
00:54:34,790 --> 00:54:36,540
你们有几个人
How many of you is in there?

975
00:54:36,550 --> 00:54:37,640
就我们俩
Just the two of us.

976
00:54:37,770 --> 00:54:39,230
但是我的搭档中枪了
But my partner's hit.

977
00:54:39,230 --> 00:54:40,300
他走不动了
And he can't walk.

978
00:54:42,000 --> 00:54:43,680
你是埃米特・昆西吗
Is that Emmet Quincy?

979
00:55:03,110 --> 00:55:04,960
你说房顶上的是个男的
You said it was a man on the roof.

980
00:55:04,960 --> 00:55:06,410
我以为是波特呢
I thought it was Potter.

981
00:55:06,770 --> 00:55:10,320
昆西  你还是一如既往的笨啊
You was always dumb, Quincy, and remain true to form.

982
00:55:10,670 --> 00:55:12,950
怎么这么多玉米糊糊啊
This here's an awful lot of sofky.

983
00:55:14,410 --> 00:55:15,860
你们在等同伙吗
You boys looking for company?

984
00:55:16,680 --> 00:55:19,200
没有  那是我们的晚饭和早饭
No, that was supper and breakfast both.

985
00:55:19,360 --> 00:55:20,960
我想早上多吃点
I like a big breakfast.

986
00:55:22,120 --> 00:55:25,180
玉米糊熟了之后会变大的
Sofky always cooks up bigger than you think.

987
00:55:25,180 --> 00:55:27,750
还有威士忌呢
And a good store of whiskey here as well.

988
00:55:28,760 --> 00:55:31,580
你们准备这么多吃的干什么
What are you boys up to, outside of cooking banquets?

989
00:55:31,580 --> 00:55:33,060
我们正在吃饭
We were just having our supper.

990
00:55:33,060 --> 00:55:35,590
这种鬼天气  我们也不知道是谁在外面
We don't know who was outside in weather like this.

991
00:55:36,080 --> 00:55:37,690
还以为是个疯子呢
Might have been some crazy man.

992
00:55:37,690 --> 00:55:39,760
谁都可以自称是法警
Anyone could say he is a marshal.

993
00:55:39,770 --> 00:55:40,870
我的腿好痛
My leg hurts.

994
00:55:40,870 --> 00:55:42,800
当然痛了
I'll bet it does.

995
00:55:47,890 --> 00:55:51,010
你上次见到奈德・彼伯是什么时候
When was the last time you see your old pard, Ned Pepper?

996
00:55:51,770 --> 00:55:54,250
不知道  他是谁啊
I do not know that. Who is he?

997
00:55:54,250 --> 00:55:56,710
你居然不记得他了
I'm surprised you don't remember him.

998
00:55:56,710 --> 00:55:58,890
他是个皮包骨  又警觉又敏捷
Skinny fellow, nervous and quick,

999
00:55:58,890 --> 00:56:00,350
他的嘴唇都烂了
his lip's all messed up.

1000
00:56:01,140 --> 00:56:03,170
还是想不起来是谁
That don't bring anybody to mind.

1001
00:56:03,170 --> 00:56:04,570
现在有个新来的
There's a new boy

1002
00:56:05,750 --> 00:56:07,800
可能在奈德手下做事
that might be running with Ned.

1003
00:56:07,880 --> 00:56:11,450
他脸上有个又黑又亮的弹痕
He got a powder mark on his face, black polish.

1004
00:56:11,660 --> 00:56:13,470
他称呼自己为切尼
Calls himself Chaney

1005
00:56:13,470 --> 00:56:15,280
有时也叫切尔姆斯福特
or Chelmsford sometimes.

1006
00:56:15,940 --> 00:56:17,730
拿一把亨利步枪
Carries a Henry rifle.

1007
00:56:17,730 --> 00:56:19,950
还是记不起来
That don't bring anybody to mind.

1008
00:56:19,950 --> 00:56:22,270
如果脸上有弹痕我应该能记住的
Black mark, I would remember that.

1009
00:56:22,900 --> 00:56:25,410
你什么都不记得了是吗  昆西
You don't remember nothing I want to know, do you Quincy?

1010
00:56:27,030 --> 00:56:28,450
你知道什么  小月
What do you know, Moon?

1011
00:56:28,450 --> 00:56:30,550
我们不认识你要找的那帮人
We don't know those boys you're looking for.

1012
00:56:30,720 --> 00:56:32,930
我不认识那帮人
I don't know those boys.

1013
00:56:33,560 --> 00:56:36,260
我知道一定告诉你  我坚信法理
I always try to help out the law.

1014
00:56:36,490 --> 00:56:38,660
等我们到史密斯堡的时候
By the time we get to Fort Smith,

1015
00:56:38,660 --> 00:56:42,080
你这条腿就会肿得像我的帽子一样粗了
that leg will be swelled up as tight as Dick's hat band.

1016
00:56:42,430 --> 00:56:43,940
这条腿就废了
It'll be mortified.

1017
00:56:43,940 --> 00:56:45,760
到时候不截肢都不行了
And they'll have to cut it off.

1018
00:56:45,770 --> 00:56:47,010
如果你活下来了
Then if you live, I'll make

1019
00:56:47,010 --> 00:56:48,990
我会让你在底特律的联邦监狱里
it two or three years in the federal house

1020
00:56:48,990 --> 00:56:51,160
-蹲个两三年  -你在威胁我
- up in Detroit, there. - You're trying to get at me.

1021
00:56:51,160 --> 00:56:53,190
他们会教你读书写字的  但是
They'll teach you how to read an write up there. But...

1022
00:56:54,530 --> 00:56:56,390
除此之外  就有你好受的了
The rest won't be so good.

1023
00:56:56,390 --> 00:56:59,200
那帮家伙连瘸子都会不放过的
Them boys, they can be hard on a gimp.

1024
00:56:59,200 --> 00:57:00,270
你在威胁我
You are trying to get at me.

1025
00:57:00,270 --> 00:57:01,290
现在
Now.

1026
00:57:01,880 --> 00:57:04,530
如果你能透露点关于奈德的消息
You give me some good information on Ned.

1027
00:57:04,530 --> 00:57:06,800
我明天就把你送回巴格比的商店
I'll take you down to Bagby's store tomorrow,

1028
00:57:06,800 --> 00:57:08,560
把你腿里的子弹取出来
get that ball taken out of your leg.

1029
00:57:08,560 --> 00:57:11,210
然后我会给你们三天时间离开这里
Then I'll give you three days to clear the Territory.

1030
00:57:11,210 --> 00:57:13,020
我们真的不认识你要找的那帮人
We don't know those boys you're looking for.

1031
00:57:14,960 --> 00:57:16,040
反正不是他的腿
It ain't his leg.

1032
00:57:16,040 --> 00:57:17,580
-我...  -你能闭嘴吗  小月
- I was... -Won't you flap your mouth, Moon?

1033
00:57:17,590 --> 00:57:20,060
我来说就可以了
It's best you let me do the talking.

1034
00:57:20,060 --> 00:57:21,650
-我要说  -我们是谨慎的捕猎者
- I would say I... - We are weary trappers.

1035
00:57:23,780 --> 00:57:25,910
你怎么会跟这个老恶棍在一起
Who worked you over with the ugly stick?

1036
00:57:25,910 --> 00:57:28,600
脸上有弹痕的那个切尼杀了我父亲
The man Chaney with the marked face, killed my father.

1037
00:57:28,600 --> 00:57:30,680
他也像你一样是个醉鬼
He's a whiskey drinker like you

1038
00:57:30,680 --> 00:57:31,900
他因为喝醉杀了我父亲
and it led to killing in the end.

1039
00:57:33,310 --> 00:57:35,710
好好回答法警的问题  他会帮你的
If you answer the Marshal's questions, he will help you.

1040
00:57:35,710 --> 00:57:37,970
我家有个很好的律师  他也会帮你的
I have a good lawyer at home, and I know he will help you too.

1041
00:57:39,220 --> 00:57:40,840
我有点搞不懂
I'm puzzled by these.

1042
00:57:40,840 --> 00:57:42,080
她为什么会在这
Why is she here?

1043
00:57:42,080 --> 00:57:46,080
乔  别听那个小兔崽子的鬼话
Joe, these people. Don't you go jawing with that runt.

1044
00:57:46,080 --> 00:57:46,760
我不喜欢你
I don't like you.

1045
00:57:46,760 --> 00:57:49,870
我希望你进监狱  我的律师才不会帮你
I hope you go to jail. My lawyer will not help you.

1046
00:57:49,870 --> 00:57:51,750
我腿疼的要昏过去了
My leg is giving me fits.

1047
00:57:51,750 --> 00:57:54,310
像你这样的年轻人不会想失去一条腿的
A young fellow like you don't want to loose his leg.

1048
00:57:54,310 --> 00:57:55,750
冷静点
Easy now.

1049
00:57:55,750 --> 00:57:57,090
他在引诱你
He's trying to get at you.

1050
00:57:57,090 --> 00:57:57,890
我从不食言
With the truth.

1051
00:57:57,890 --> 00:57:59,500
前天我们看到奈德和海斯了
We seen Ned and Hayes two days ago.

1052
00:57:59,500 --> 00:58:02,060
你脑子坏了吗  你再说我就杀了你
Don't you act the fool, if you blow I will kill you.

1053
00:58:02,060 --> 00:58:03,770
我受够了  我需要个医生
I'm played out, I need a doctor.

1054
00:58:03,770 --> 00:58:05,660
我们前天碰到奈德和Hays了
We met Ned and Hayes two days ago.

1055
00:58:20,800 --> 00:58:21,990
该死的
God damn it.

1056
00:58:29,410 --> 00:58:30,530
天啊
Oh lord.

1057
00:58:31,500 --> 00:58:32,660
我要死了
I'm dying.

1058
00:58:34,980 --> 00:58:36,050
快想想办法
Do something.

1059
00:58:36,230 --> 00:58:37,310
救救我
Help me.

1060
00:58:37,940 --> 00:58:39,610
我也无计可施了  孩子
I can do nothing for you, son.

1061
00:58:40,070 --> 00:58:42,650
你的伙伴要杀你  我已经替你报仇了
You pard has killed you, and I've done for him.

1062
00:58:42,650 --> 00:58:44,550
别让我死在这里
Don't leave me lying here.

1063
00:58:45,180 --> 00:58:47,060
别让狼把我吃掉的
Don't let the wolves rip me up.

1064
00:58:47,340 --> 00:58:49,060
我会把你安葬的
I'll see you're buried right.

1065
00:58:49,060 --> 00:58:51,160
跟我说说奈德  你在哪儿看到他了
You tell me about Ned, where'd you see him?

1066
00:58:51,960 --> 00:58:53,480
前天
Two days ago.

1067
00:58:53,490 --> 00:58:54,760
在巴格比的商店
Bagby's store.

1068
00:58:55,520 --> 00:58:59,210
他们今晚要来这里换马并拿些玉米糊
They are coming here tonight to get remounts, and sofky.

1069
00:59:00,630 --> 00:59:03,940
他们刚在御夫座铁路交叉处抢了飞之凯蒂
They just robbed the Katy Flyer at Wagoner's Switch.

1070
00:59:00,630 --> 00:59:03,940
飞之凯蒂: 最早拥有名字的火车
途径密苏里州  堪萨斯州  德克萨斯州

1071
00:59:04,730 --> 00:59:06,310
我要死了
I'm gone.

1072
00:59:09,080 --> 00:59:11,800
给我的兄弟乔治・加勒特捎个信
Send the news to my brother, George Garrett.

1073
00:59:12,190 --> 00:59:15,840
他在德州南部做卫理公会巡回牧师
He is a Methodist circuit rider in South Texas.

1074
00:59:15,840 --> 00:59:18,330
我要不要告诉他你是个逃犯
Shall I tell him you was outlawed up.

1075
00:59:18,330 --> 00:59:19,460
无所谓了
It don't matter.

1076
00:59:19,470 --> 00:59:21,670
他知道的
He knows I'm on the scout.

1077
00:59:23,600 --> 00:59:26,840
我会在荣耀之路上和他相见的
I will meet him later, walking the streets of Glory.

1078
00:59:28,360 --> 00:59:30,720
别碰见昆西
Well don't be looking for Quincy.

1079
00:59:43,350 --> 00:59:44,540
他们来了之后我们怎么干
What do we do when they get here?

1080
00:59:44,540 --> 00:59:46,080
等他们自己送上门
Well, they will ride up.

1081
00:59:46,080 --> 00:59:48,410
到时候我们来一个瓮中捉鳖
What we want is to get them all in the dugout.

1082
00:59:49,270 --> 00:59:50,880
我会干掉最后一个进去的人
I'll kill the last one that goes in,

1083
00:59:50,880 --> 00:59:52,410
之后他们就成瓮中之鳖了
then we will have them in a barrel.

1084
00:59:52,860 --> 00:59:54,070
你在他们身后放冷枪吗
You will shoot them in the back?

1085
00:59:54,080 --> 00:59:57,010
这样才能给他们个下马威
It will give them to know our intention is serious.

1086
00:59:57,530 --> 00:59:58,990
然后我会喊话
Then I will call down

1087
00:59:59,560 --> 01:00:01,720
看看我们能不能活捉他们
see if they'll be taken alive.

1088
01:00:02,330 --> 01:00:04,320
如果抓不到活的
If they won't.

1089
01:00:04,320 --> 01:00:06,010
他们一出来我就开枪
I'll shoot them as they come out.

1090
01:00:07,560 --> 01:00:08,870
干掉他们中的三个
I'm hopeful that three of their party being dead

1091
01:00:08,870 --> 01:00:10,870
估计他们也就没胆了
will take the starch out of them.

1092
01:00:13,550 --> 01:00:15,210
你看上去很沉着
You display great poise.

1093
01:00:18,000 --> 01:00:19,870
这跟打火鸡没什么两样
Aw,it is just a turkey shoot.

1094
01:00:22,090 --> 01:00:25,480
有一次在新墨西哥州
There was one time, in New Mexico,

1095
01:00:25,930 --> 01:00:28,460
我们被七个人追
we was being pursued by seven men.

1096
01:00:28,970 --> 01:00:31,690
我把马调了个头 然后用牙咬住缰绳
I turned Bo around and taken them reins in my teeth,

1097
01:00:31,700 --> 01:00:32,930
朝着他们直冲过去
and rode right at them boys.

1098
01:00:32,930 --> 01:00:35,620
拿我马鞍里的两把海军六号朝他们开火
Firing them two navy sixes I carry in my saddle.

1099
01:00:36,560 --> 01:00:39,920
希望他们真是如我所想的那样
Well.. I guess they was all married men who

1100
01:00:39,920 --> 01:00:42,680
都有老婆了  非常顾家  不能丢失性命
loved their families as they scattered and run for home.

1101
01:00:43,280 --> 01:00:44,700
这真的难以置信
Well that is hard to believe.

1102
01:00:44,700 --> 01:00:47,330
-什么难以置信  -你居然一挑七啊
- What is? - One man riding at seven.

1103
01:00:47,330 --> 01:00:48,770
这是真的
Well, it's true.

1104
01:00:49,140 --> 01:00:51,680
当你足够快足够勇猛的时候
You go for a man hard enough and fast enough,

1105
01:00:51,800 --> 01:00:53,260
你的对手是不会想己方有多少人的
You don't have time to think about

1106
01:00:53,260 --> 01:00:55,670
他只会考虑他自己
how many is with him, he thinks about himself.

1107
01:00:56,120 --> 01:00:59,160
考虑如何阻挡即将到来的狂风暴雨
How he may get clear of the wrath that's about to set down on you.

1108
01:01:00,560 --> 01:01:01,650
他们为什么要追你呢
Why were they pursuing you?

1109
01:01:04,910 --> 01:01:06,720
我抢劫了一个放高利贷的银行
I robbed a high-interest bank.

1110
01:01:07,740 --> 01:01:09,490
我总不能去抢小偷吧
Can't rob a thief, can you?

1111
01:01:10,530 --> 01:01:12,060
我从不抢平民的钱
Never robbed a citizen.

1112
01:01:12,060 --> 01:01:13,500
连一块表都没抢过
Never took a man's watch.

1113
01:01:13,500 --> 01:01:14,500
抢谁都不对
It is all stealing.

1114
01:01:15,080 --> 01:01:17,700
那帮新墨西哥州的人也这么想
That's the position they took in New Mexico.

1115
01:01:29,930 --> 01:01:31,400
就一个人
One man.

1116
01:01:32,220 --> 01:01:34,840
没想到他们会派人过来探风
I didn't figure them to send a scout.

1117
01:01:53,900 --> 01:01:55,660
该死的
Damn.

1118
01:01:58,620 --> 01:02:00,920
他是勒波义夫
It is LeBoeuf.

1119
01:02:06,540 --> 01:02:08,440
警官  我们必须得去提醒他
Oh, we have to warn him, Marshal.

1120
01:02:16,470 --> 01:02:17,470
来不及了
Too late.

1121
01:02:47,910 --> 01:02:49,450
我们该怎么办啊  警官
What do we do, Marshal?

1122
01:02:49,890 --> 01:02:52,220
静观其变  他在干什么
We sit. What does he do?

1123
01:03:11,800 --> 01:03:14,640
那个穿羊皮衣服的小子就是狗屎运奈德
Him in the woolly chaps, is Lucky Ned.

1124
01:03:25,090 --> 01:03:26,540
就是现在
Well, that's that.

1125
01:04:19,330 --> 01:04:21,050
计划失败
Well that didn't pan out.

1126
01:04:28,420 --> 01:04:30,810
你把我的计划全毁了  伙计
You managed to put a kink in my rope, partner.

1127
01:04:32,240 --> 01:04:34,160
我伤的很严重
Ah, I'm severely injured.

1128
01:04:34,160 --> 01:04:36,130
伤的不轻呢
Yes, you got rocks on.

1129
01:04:36,130 --> 01:04:37,790
我中枪了
I was also shot.

1130
01:04:38,080 --> 01:04:39,420
而且是被来复枪打中
By a rifle.

1131
01:04:39,420 --> 01:04:40,480
很有可能
Well that's quite possible.

1132
01:04:40,480 --> 01:04:42,810
我没能够按照原计划行动
The scheme did not developed as I had planned.

1133
01:04:44,650 --> 01:04:47,500
你肩膀中枪了  好在子弹穿过去了
You've been shot in the shoulder, but the bullet passed through.

1134
01:04:48,150 --> 01:04:49,230
你嘴怎么了
What happened to your mouth?

1135
01:04:50,110 --> 01:04:52,040
我可能咬着自己了
I believe I bit myself.

1136
01:04:52,450 --> 01:04:55,340
掉了几颗牙  果真啊
Couple of teeth loose, and ah yeah.

1137
01:04:55,840 --> 01:04:57,980
舌头都快被咬断了
Tongue bit almost through.

1138
01:04:57,980 --> 01:05:00,720
你想我把它留在里面还是猛的拔出来
You want to see if it'll knit or should I just yank it free.

1139
01:05:01,190 --> 01:05:02,620
我认识一个赶马的人
I know a teamster.

1140
01:05:02,620 --> 01:05:04,610
他从马背上摔下来的时候把舌头咬断了
Bit his tongue off as he was thrown from a horse.

1141
01:05:04,610 --> 01:05:07,700
过了很长时间才能说话
After a time he learned to make himself more or less understood.

1142
01:05:07,700 --> 01:05:08,790
我还是把它弄出来吧
I'll just yank it free.

1143
01:05:10,830 --> 01:05:11,970
现在怎么样了
What's that now.

1144
01:05:12,700 --> 01:05:13,860
现在怎么样了
What's that now?

1145
01:05:13,860 --> 01:05:15,750
会自己愈合的
Knit. It will knit.

1146
01:05:15,760 --> 01:05:16,860
好极了
Ah, very well.

1147
01:05:17,550 --> 01:05:20,150
舌头上的伤口可包扎不了
It's impossible to bind a tongue wound.

1148
01:05:20,150 --> 01:05:22,860
真不巧  我们刚才还碰到个医生呢
Too bad, we just ran across a doctor.

1149
01:05:23,820 --> 01:05:25,660
-警官  -但是我们不知道他往哪走了
- Marshal? - Of sorts, but we did not know where he was headed.

1150
01:05:25,660 --> 01:05:27,920
我也看到他了  所以我才过来的
I saw him too, that's how I came to be here.

1151
01:05:28,870 --> 01:05:30,570
这些人里没有切尼
Neither of these men are Chaney.

1152
01:05:30,910 --> 01:05:32,750
我知道  这几个人我都认识
I know it, I know them both.

1153
01:05:33,390 --> 01:05:35,380
那个长的很丑的是憧伞ずＫ
That ugly one is Coke Hayes.

1154
01:05:35,380 --> 01:05:38,450
这个更丑的是克莱门特・帕马利
Him uglier stiff is Clement Parmalee.

1155
01:05:38,450 --> 01:05:39,990
帕马利和他的兄弟们
Parmalee and his brothers

1156
01:05:39,990 --> 01:05:42,890
在旋梯山有一个老窝
have a silver claim in the Winding Stair Mountains.

1157
01:05:42,890 --> 01:05:45,420
狗屎运奈德的同伙肯定在那等他们
And I'll bet that's where Lucky Ned's gang is waiting.

1158
01:05:45,420 --> 01:05:48,210
我们今晚在这过夜  明早再去找他们
Well, we'll sleep here, follow in the morning.

1159
01:05:48,490 --> 01:05:50,640
但我们答应过他要把他安葬好的
But we promised to bury the poor soul inside.

1160
01:05:50,790 --> 01:05:52,250
地太硬了
Ground is too hard.

1161
01:05:52,740 --> 01:05:54,320
他要是想安葬的比较风光的话
That man wanted a decent burial,

1162
01:05:54,320 --> 01:05:56,630
他应该等到夏天再死
he should have gotten himself killed in summer.

1163
01:06:01,180 --> 01:06:02,890
晚安  小黑
Sleep well, Little Blackie.

1164
01:06:02,890 --> 01:06:05,950
我的直觉告诉我  明天就能找到他了
I have a notion that tomorrow we will reach our object.

1165
01:06:06,650 --> 01:06:08,110
我们紧随其后
We're hot on the trail.

1166
01:06:08,970 --> 01:06:12,200
我们会在旋梯山追上汤姆・切尼的
Seems that we'll overtake Tom Chaney in the Winding Stairs Mountains.

1167
01:06:13,000 --> 01:06:14,740
他到时候肯定不会好受
I would not want to be in his shoes.

1168
01:06:24,390 --> 01:06:26,900
据我了解  切尼和
As I understand it, Chaney or

1169
01:06:26,900 --> 01:06:29,960
切尔姆斯福特的名字是他在德州常用的
Chelmsford, as he called himself in Texas.

1170
01:06:30,270 --> 01:06:31,900
杀了州议员的狗
Shot the senator's dog.

1171
01:06:32,160 --> 01:06:34,300
当州议员要告他的时候
When the Senator remonstrated

1172
01:06:34,300 --> 01:06:35,790
切尔姆斯福特把他也给杀了
Chelmsford shot him as well.

1173
01:06:36,150 --> 01:06:38,190
你现在也许会说
Now you could argue that the shooting

1174
01:06:38,190 --> 01:06:41,160
枪杀那条狗是禁止的
of the dog was clearly an instance of malum prohibitum.

1175
01:06:41,160 --> 01:06:42,400
但枪杀议员
But the shooting of the senator

1176
01:06:42,400 --> 01:06:44,940
无疑是个违法的案例
is indubitably a instance of malum in se.

1177
01:06:45,260 --> 01:06:47,010
违什么
Malum in what?

1178
01:06:47,010 --> 01:06:48,330
违法的
Malum in se.

1179
01:06:48,330 --> 01:06:51,620
两者的区别一个是事情本身的错误
The distinction is between an act that is wrong within itself.

1180
01:06:51,620 --> 01:06:54,900
另外一个是违反法律规定和道德约束的
And an act that is wrong according to our laws and mores.

1181
01:06:54,900 --> 01:06:56,070
是拉丁语
It is Latin.

1182
01:06:57,500 --> 01:06:59,130
我实在吃惊
I'm struck,

1183
01:06:59,320 --> 01:07:00,000
你不但挨了枪子  还被人蹂躏成这个样
that LeBoeuf had been shot, trampled

1184
01:07:00,010 --> 01:07:04,800
舌头差点都断了
and nearly severed his tongue.

1185
01:07:05,840 --> 01:07:08,080
这都堵不住你的嘴
Not only does he not cease to talk,

1186
01:07:08,080 --> 01:07:10,310
你说话说的还挺溜
but he spills the banks of English.

1187
01:07:15,170 --> 01:07:18,200
有一次我离切尔姆斯福特只有两百多米
I was within three hundred yards of Chelmsford once.

1188
01:07:19,420 --> 01:07:21,100
可能是最近的一次了
The closest I have been.

1189
01:07:21,910 --> 01:07:24,600
并且在我的夏普斯卡宾枪的射程内
With a Sharps carbine that is within range.

1190
01:07:25,050 --> 01:07:29,310
我在马上  可以立马开枪
But I was mounted, and had the choice of firing off-hand.

1191
01:07:29,310 --> 01:07:31,290
也可以下马站立开枪
or dismounting and shoot from the rest.

1192
01:07:31,290 --> 01:07:34,240
不过这样他就和我拉开距离了
which would allow Chelmsford to augment the distance.

1193
01:07:35,990 --> 01:07:37,410
我还是在马上开枪了
I fired mounted.

1194
01:07:39,640 --> 01:07:40,980
但是打偏了
And fired wide.

1195
01:07:45,600 --> 01:07:47,620
如果你让枪每天都睡大觉
You could not hit a man at three hundred yards

1196
01:07:47,620 --> 01:07:50,430
怎么可能射中一个两百多米远的人
if your gun was resting on your Gibraltar.

1197
01:07:51,090 --> 01:07:54,720
夏普斯卡宾枪拥有强大的威力和精准度
A Sharps carbine is an instrument of uncanny power and precision.

1198
01:07:54,720 --> 01:07:57,510
我可没说枪不行
I've no doubt that the gun is sound.

1199
01:07:58,640 --> 01:08:03,040
我衣衫褴褛  口无遮拦
My clothes are all ragged and my language is rough.

1200
01:08:03,040 --> 01:08:07,710
就连我的面包也从来不服软
My bread is corn dodgers, both solid and tough

1201
01:08:07,710 --> 01:08:12,530
我的生活快乐又美好
And yet I'm happy, and live at my ease

1202
01:08:12,530 --> 01:08:16,850
就像高粱糖浆  培根和奶酪
On sorghum molasses, and bacon, and cheese

1203
01:08:16,850 --> 01:08:19,110
《格里尔县》  班特勒作曲
Greer county, Bantler.

1204
01:08:22,470 --> 01:08:24,070
我不相信他昨晚睡觉了
I do not believe he slept.

1205
01:08:32,360 --> 01:08:34,980
史密斯堡不远了  勒波义夫
Fort Smith is a healthy distance, LeBoeuf.

1206
01:08:34,980 --> 01:08:37,160
但是我想让你的马往切斯特城的方向走
But I would encourage the creature you ride to head Chester.

1207
01:08:38,650 --> 01:08:41,640
一只手的家伙只会拖我们后腿
Out here a one-armed man look like an easy prey.

1208
01:08:42,580 --> 01:08:45,180
一只眼睛枪法不准的家伙
And a one-eyed man who can't shoot.

1209
01:08:45,180 --> 01:08:47,130
你怎么不回去呢  考伯恩
Why don't you turn back, Cogburn?

1210
01:08:47,130 --> 01:08:48,410
我可得去
I'll do fine.

1211
01:08:48,410 --> 01:08:51,990
我知道帕马利的老窝在哪  我又没受伤
I know where the Parmalee's claim is. I'm uninjured,

1212
01:08:51,990 --> 01:08:55,330
我粮食充足  再说我们分道扬镳了的
well provisioned and we agree to separate.

1213
01:08:55,530 --> 01:08:58,030
你取消合约良心会不安的
In conscience you cannot shite our agreement.

1214
01:08:58,040 --> 01:08:59,670
而且是你开枪打伤了我
You're the one that shot me.

1215
01:08:59,670 --> 01:09:01,720
勒波义夫先生说得有道理  警官
Mr. LeBoeuf has a point, Marshal.

1216
01:09:01,720 --> 01:09:03,060
在竞赛中
It is unfair leg-up in any

1217
01:09:03,060 --> 01:09:05,220
朝对手开枪可有失公平
competition to shoot your opposite number.

1218
01:09:05,720 --> 01:09:06,760
他妈的  我不能接受
God damn it. I do not

1219
01:09:06,770 --> 01:09:08,950
你说是我开枪打了勒波义夫
accept it as a given that I did shoot LeBoeuf.

1220
01:09:08,950 --> 01:09:10,970
当时那么多枪都响了
There were plenty of guns going off.

1221
01:09:10,970 --> 01:09:13,360
我听到来福枪响了  而且感觉到了子弹
I heard the rifle, and I felt the ball.

1222
01:09:13,360 --> 01:09:15,220
你打偏了  考伯恩
You missed your shot, Cogburn.

1223
01:09:15,220 --> 01:09:16,620
我会打偏吗
Missed my shot!

1224
01:09:16,620 --> 01:09:20,390
你缺只眼睛可比我缺之手差多了
You are more handicapped without the eye, then I without the arm.

1225
01:09:20,570 --> 01:09:23,210
我能射中六十米外的蚊子眼睛
I can hit a gnat's eye at ninety yards.

1226
01:09:34,780 --> 01:09:37,670
那个中国佬又卖了我一堆水货子弹
That chinaman is running them cheap shells on me again.

1227
01:09:37,670 --> 01:09:40,010
我以为你要说  太阳刺进了你的双眼呢
I thought you were going to say, the sun was in your eyes.

1228
01:09:40,660 --> 01:09:43,310
对了  你只有一只眼睛
That is to say, "Your eye".

1229
01:10:28,010 --> 01:10:29,620
一次中两个
Two at one time.

1230
01:10:44,420 --> 01:10:46,470
我扔高一点
I will chuck one high.

1231
01:10:46,470 --> 01:10:47,650
你别开枪
Hold fire.

1232
01:10:56,210 --> 01:10:58,420
-中了  -中了
- There. - There?

1233
01:10:58,420 --> 01:11:00,590
-是我打中的  -是你吗
- My bullet. - Your bullet?

1234
01:11:00,600 --> 01:11:03,560
你要是能打中还会误伤我的肩膀吗
If you hit what you aim at, explain my shoulder.

1235
01:11:03,560 --> 01:11:05,180
先生们  在大草原上比赛射面包
Gentlemen, shooting corn bread out here on

1236
01:11:05,180 --> 01:11:07,600
不能帮我们找到彼伯那帮人
the prairie is getting us no closer to the Pepper gang.

1237
01:11:07,600 --> 01:11:10,040
再来一次  等着瞧
One more. This will prove it.

1238
01:11:10,040 --> 01:11:11,720
请你别开枪
Please hold fire.

1239
01:12:36,780 --> 01:12:38,540
这样就能找到回去的路
Find our way back.

1240
01:12:53,880 --> 01:12:54,880
狗屎运奈德
Lucky Ned?

1241
01:13:06,400 --> 01:13:07,750
狗屎运奈德
Lucky Ned!

1242
01:13:10,250 --> 01:13:11,960
真不赖啊  考伯恩
Very good, Cogburn.

1243
01:13:11,960 --> 01:13:13,260
现在怎么办
Now what?

1244
01:13:19,510 --> 01:13:21,210
该死的
Oh, god damn it.

1245
01:13:21,740 --> 01:13:24,750
考伯恩才不想我吃他的粮食
Cogburn does not want me to eat out of his store.

1246
01:13:24,750 --> 01:13:25,450
别犯傻了
That is silly.

1247
01:13:25,450 --> 01:13:27,660
你一整天都没吃了  而且这些是我的
You have not eaten the whole day,and it is my store not his.

1248
01:13:27,660 --> 01:13:29,280
饿死他好了
Let him starve.

1249
01:13:31,260 --> 01:13:32,960
他既没追踪
He did not track.

1250
01:13:32,970 --> 01:13:34,140
也没开过枪
He did not shoot.

1251
01:13:34,450 --> 01:13:36,100
还好意思吃东西
Accepting food stuffs.

1252
01:13:36,100 --> 01:13:37,990
这都是你自找的
That was your initiative.

1253
01:13:38,000 --> 01:13:38,750
他一点力都没出
He did not contribute.

1254
01:13:39,300 --> 01:13:43,070
他是个只会挨枪子的人
He's a man, who walks in front of bullets.

1255
01:13:43,180 --> 01:13:45,820
我们躲在掩护后面安全地开枪的时候
Mr. LeBoeuf drew single-handed upon the Lucky Ned Pepper gang

1256
01:13:45,820 --> 01:13:47,310
勒波义夫在和狗屎运奈德他们单打独斗
while we fired safely from cover.

1257
01:13:47,700 --> 01:13:50,290
-我们  -你不应该这么说他
- We? - It is unfair to indict a man,

1258
01:13:50,290 --> 01:13:52,000
尤其当他的下巴都肿了
when his jaw is swollen, and tongue

1259
01:13:52,000 --> 01:13:54,690
舌头都快断了  他根本没法辩护
mangled and is therefore unable to rise to his defense.

1260
01:13:54,700 --> 01:13:56,010
我可以为我自己辩护的
I can speak for myself.

1261
01:13:56,320 --> 01:13:58,320
只不过对于像你这种低级醉鬼
I'm hardly obliged to answer

1262
01:13:58,320 --> 01:14:01,360
我才懒得和你吵架呢
the ravings of a drunkard who is beneath me.

1263
01:14:02,840 --> 01:14:06,440
我会到其他的地方另起炉灶的
I shall make my own camp elsewhere.

1264
01:14:07,610 --> 01:14:10,330
你才什么都没干呢  考伯恩
It is you who have nothing to offer, Cogburn.

1265
01:14:10,690 --> 01:14:12,570
你好意思吗
A sad picture indeed.

1266
01:14:12,840 --> 01:14:14,900
这不再是追踪犯人了
This is no longer a man hunt.

1267
01:14:14,900 --> 01:14:16,280
是自我堕落
It is a debauch.

1268
01:14:16,810 --> 01:14:18,410
德州骑警队员
The Texas Ranger

1269
01:14:18,420 --> 01:14:20,640
将独自去完成任务
presses on, alone.

1270
01:14:23,070 --> 01:14:24,410
把这个小姑娘带走
Take the girl.

1271
01:14:24,410 --> 01:14:25,650
我不干了
I bow out.

1272
01:14:28,290 --> 01:14:29,690
早知现在  何必当初
A fine thing to decide once you

1273
01:14:29,690 --> 01:14:31,870
在这荒芜之地撒下她不管吗
brought her in the middle of the Choctaw Nation.

1274
01:14:31,870 --> 01:14:33,760
我不干了  我金盆洗手了
I bow out, I wash my hands.

1275
01:14:33,760 --> 01:14:35,780
先生们  我们不能在这个时候闹翻啊
Gentlemen we cannot fall out in this fashion.

1276
01:14:35,780 --> 01:14:38,700
我们马上就要抓到汤姆・切尼了
Not so close to our goal, with Tom Chaney nearly in hand.

1277
01:14:38,700 --> 01:14:40,810
抓到个屁
In hand?

1278
01:14:41,110 --> 01:14:42,610
如果他现在没被埋在
If he is not in a shallow grave

1279
01:14:42,610 --> 01:14:45,250
从这去史密斯堡路上的坟堆里
somewhere between here and Fort Smith.

1280
01:14:45,260 --> 01:14:46,620
那就是他逃跑了
He is gone.

1281
01:14:47,090 --> 01:14:48,230
跑到天涯海角去了
Long gone.

1282
01:14:48,860 --> 01:14:52,020
这还要归功于勒波义夫先生 我们打偏了
Thanks to Mr. LeBoeuf, we missed our shot.

1283
01:14:52,420 --> 01:14:54,650
我们已经打草惊蛇了
We have barked and the birds have flown.

1284
01:14:54,930 --> 01:14:56,690
跑了  跑了  跑了
Gone, gone, gone.

1285
01:14:57,050 --> 01:14:59,290
狗屎运奈德的大军逃跑了
Lucky Ned's cohort gone.

1286
01:14:59,300 --> 01:15:01,080
你的五十美金也泡汤了
Your fifty dollars, gone.

1287
01:15:01,080 --> 01:15:02,560
跟我的威士忌一起泡汤了
Gone with whiskey.

1288
01:15:02,580 --> 01:15:04,320
这多显而易见啊
Seized in evidence.

1289
01:15:05,110 --> 01:15:07,580
就算他们留下踪迹也追不上了
The trail is cold if ever there was one.

1290
01:15:10,680 --> 01:15:12,850
我  我真是个糊涂的老头
I'm....I'm a foolish old man

1291
01:15:12,850 --> 01:15:16,920
被人拉进这么个徒劳无功的追捕
who'd been drawn into a wild goose chase.

1292
01:15:17,280 --> 01:15:21,350
居然还是被个悍妇和一个傻子拉进来的
by a harpy in trousers, and a nincompoop.

1293
01:15:22,090 --> 01:15:24,730
勒波义夫先生
Ah, Mr. LeBoeuf.

1294
01:15:24,740 --> 01:15:27,930
他爱在这儿待多久就待多久吧
He can wander the Choctaw Nation for as long as he likes.

1295
01:15:27,930 --> 01:15:30,420
当地的土著印第安人或许还把他当兄弟呢
Perhaps the local Indians will take him in.

1296
01:15:30,760 --> 01:15:33,500
他能说会道  没准能当上酋长呢
Honor his gibbering by making him Chief.

1297
01:15:34,630 --> 01:15:37,230
小妹妹  你爱去哪儿就去哪儿吧
You sister, may go where you like.

1298
01:15:38,100 --> 01:15:40,510
我们的合同终止了
Our engagement is terminated.

1299
01:15:42,600 --> 01:15:43,940
我不干了
I bow out.

1300
01:15:51,870 --> 01:15:52,970
我和你去
I'm going with you.

1301
01:15:53,290 --> 01:15:55,410
不行  这不可能
No, that is not possible.

1302
01:15:55,540 --> 01:15:57,120
我拖了你的后腿吗
Have I held you back?

1303
01:15:57,880 --> 01:16:00,960
我有把我会用的柯尔特龙骑兵左轮手枪
I have a Colt's Dragoon revolver, which I know how to use.

1304
01:16:01,260 --> 01:16:03,900
我不会给你带来负担
And I will be no more of a burden to you, as I was to the Marshal.

1305
01:16:03,900 --> 01:16:05,170
我担心的不是这个
That's not my worry.

1306
01:16:05,500 --> 01:16:07,470
你很勇敢
You've earned your spurs.

1307
01:16:07,470 --> 01:16:08,590
你已经证明了
That is clear now.

1308
01:16:09,250 --> 01:16:12,370
你已经成为一名追踪高手了
You've been an regular old hand on the trail.

1309
01:16:13,610 --> 01:16:15,290
但是考伯恩说的对
But Cogburn's right.

1310
01:16:15,290 --> 01:16:18,150
虽然我刚才没当着他的面承认
Even if I will not give him the satisfaction of consenting it.

1311
01:16:19,790 --> 01:16:21,330
确实追不上了
The trail is cold.

1312
01:16:22,930 --> 01:16:27,380
而且我也伤得不轻
And I am, considerably diminished.

1313
01:16:27,760 --> 01:16:29,050
你追踪切尼那么久了
How can you give up now,

1314
01:16:29,050 --> 01:16:31,240
怎么能说放弃就放弃呢
after the many months you've dedicated to finding Chaney?

1315
01:16:32,330 --> 01:16:34,070
你展示出了极大的决心
You have shown great determination.

1316
01:16:35,690 --> 01:16:37,100
我之前小看你了
I misjudged you.

1317
01:16:41,100 --> 01:16:42,540
我挑错人了
I picked the wrong man.

1318
01:16:46,320 --> 01:16:49,820
如果我们还有办法的话  我愿意帮你
I would go on with your company, if there were a clear way to go.

1319
01:16:51,690 --> 01:16:53,830
但我们只能在黑暗中摸索
But we'd be striking out blindly.

1320
01:16:55,560 --> 01:16:56,910
切尔姆斯福特已经逃跑了
Chelmsford's gone.

1321
01:16:58,500 --> 01:17:00,390
我们都追到这天荒地末了
We chased him right off the map.

1322
01:17:01,700 --> 01:17:03,000
这事就这样
There is nothing for it.

1323
01:17:07,520 --> 01:17:08,950
我回德州了
I'm bound for Texas.

1324
01:17:10,520 --> 01:17:12,180
你也该回家了
It's time for you to go home, too.

1325
01:17:13,420 --> 01:17:15,430
等警官清醒之后
The Marshal, when he sobers,

1326
01:17:17,090 --> 01:17:18,500
你就该回去了
is your way back.

1327
01:17:18,500 --> 01:17:20,410
我不回去  没找到切尼就不回去  
I will not go back. Not without Chaney,

1328
01:17:20,410 --> 01:17:21,310
生要见人  死要见尸
dead or alive.

1329
01:17:25,010 --> 01:17:26,790
我也看错你了
I misjudged you as well.

1330
01:17:29,940 --> 01:17:31,520
来握个手吧
I extend my hand.

1331
01:17:32,250 --> 01:17:33,770
勒波义夫先生  求你了
Mr. LeBoeuf! Please!

1332
01:17:46,550 --> 01:17:48,050
再会
Adios.

1333
01:19:36,560 --> 01:19:37,860
我认识你
I know you.

1334
01:19:41,240 --> 01:19:42,580
你叫麦蒂
Your name is Mattie.

1335
01:19:42,660 --> 01:19:45,010
你是小麦蒂  那个记账员
You're little Mattie, the bookkeeper.

1336
01:19:45,010 --> 01:19:48,230
真巧啊
Isn't that something.

1337
01:19:48,230 --> 01:19:49,850
是的  而且我认识你  汤姆・切尼
Yes, and I know you, Tom Chaney.

1338
01:19:52,850 --> 01:19:54,200
你在这干什么
What are you doing out here?

1339
01:19:54,570 --> 01:19:55,860
来打点水
Come to fetch some water.

1340
01:19:55,860 --> 01:19:58,050
那你在这山里干什么
Oh, then what are you doing in these mountains, here?

1341
01:19:58,050 --> 01:19:59,930
虽然还没被正式任命
Well I have not been formally deputized,

1342
01:19:59,930 --> 01:20:02,110
但我是受命于鲁本・考伯恩警官
but I am acting as an agent for Marshal Reuben Cogburn

1343
01:20:02,110 --> 01:20:03,360
和帕克法官
and Judge Parker's court.

1344
01:20:09,510 --> 01:20:11,680
我要把你带回史密斯堡
I have come to take you back to Fort Smith.

1345
01:20:17,420 --> 01:20:19,110
我不去
Well I will not go.

1346
01:20:19,110 --> 01:20:20,110
你觉得怎么样
How do you like that?

1347
01:20:20,120 --> 01:20:23,300
那边有一治安团的警官会抓你去的
There is a posse of officers up there who will force you to go.

1348
01:20:23,750 --> 01:20:25,590
有意思
That is interesting news.

1349
01:20:25,590 --> 01:20:26,760
那边有多少人
And how many is up there?

1350
01:20:27,250 --> 01:20:28,530
五十个左右
Right around fifty.

1351
01:20:28,940 --> 01:20:30,780
他们都武器精良  志在必得
They're all well armed and they mean business.

1352
01:20:31,490 --> 01:20:32,820
现在我要你渡过小溪
What I want you to do now is come on across the creek

1353
01:20:32,820 --> 01:20:34,790
从我面前走到那座山上去
and walk in front of me up that hill.

1354
01:20:35,520 --> 01:20:38,880
我还是让那些警官来抓我吧
I think I will oblige the officers to come after me.

1355
01:20:39,690 --> 01:20:41,790
如果你不照着做  我就得开枪了
Well if you refuse to go, then I'll have to shoot you.

1356
01:20:42,460 --> 01:20:43,460
噢
Oh.

1357
01:20:43,460 --> 01:20:45,730
那你最好给枪上膛
Well you had better cock your piece.

1358
01:20:48,050 --> 01:20:49,090
一直向后扳
All the way back.

1359
01:20:50,410 --> 01:20:52,670
-直到锁住  -我知道怎么做
- Til it locks. - I know how to do it.

1360
01:20:53,340 --> 01:20:54,610
你不打算跟我走?
You will not go with me?

1361
01:20:54,610 --> 01:20:56,100
不  恰恰相反
Naw, it's just the other way around.

1362
01:20:56,100 --> 01:20:57,350
你得跟我走
You're going with me.

1363
01:20:57,920 --> 01:20:58,920
我要...
I will...AAAH!

1364
01:21:08,170 --> 01:21:10,240
我没想到你会开枪
I did not think you would do it.

1365
01:21:10,240 --> 01:21:13,580
-现在呢  -我有根肋骨断了
- What do you think now? - One of my short ribs is broken.

1366
01:21:13,580 --> 01:21:15,990
我爸爸想帮助你  你却杀了他
You killed my father when he was trying to help you.

1367
01:21:16,410 --> 01:21:17,190
我有一个你从他那偷的金币
I have one of the gold pieces you stole from him.

1368
01:21:17,190 --> 01:21:18,310
现在把另一个也给我
Now give me the other.

1369
01:21:18,610 --> 01:21:20,610
-我干什么都不顺  -麦蒂
- Nothing has gone right for me. - MATTIE!

1370
01:21:20,610 --> 01:21:22,080
我在这下面
I'm down here.

1371
01:21:22,080 --> 01:21:23,700
现在居然被个孩子打中了
Now I'm shot by a child.

1372
01:21:23,700 --> 01:21:25,300
我抓住切尼了
Chaney is taken into custody!

1373
01:21:31,840 --> 01:21:32,840
快救我
Help me.

1374
01:21:32,840 --> 01:21:33,870
麦蒂
Mattie!

1375
01:21:36,810 --> 01:21:37,810
警官
Marshal.

1376
01:21:44,760 --> 01:21:45,990
把马牵上  快走
Take them horses you got and move!

1377
01:21:52,010 --> 01:21:54,610
汤姆  到那山上去  别停下
Tom, get on up that hill! Don't you stop..

1378
01:21:58,320 --> 01:21:59,410
下面都是些什么人
Who all is down there?

1379
01:21:59,430 --> 01:22:01,380
考伯恩和其他五十个警官
Marshal Cogburn and fifty more officers.

1380
01:22:07,820 --> 01:22:10,220
再敢撒谎  我打穿你的头
Tell me another lie and I will stove your head in!

1381
01:22:10,750 --> 01:22:12,250
只有一个法警
Just the Marshal.

1382
01:22:13,970 --> 01:22:15,410
大公鸡
Rooster.

1383
01:22:17,520 --> 01:22:18,550
考伯恩
Cogburn!

1384
01:22:19,130 --> 01:22:20,390
听得见吗
You hear me?

1385
01:22:23,630 --> 01:22:25,270
回答我  大公鸡
You answer me, Rooster!

1386
01:22:26,450 --> 01:22:28,010
我要杀了这姑娘
I will kill this girl!

1387
01:22:28,400 --> 01:22:29,720
你知道我干得出来
You know I will do it!

1388
01:22:31,460 --> 01:22:32,890
她对我来说什么也不是  
The girl is nothing to me!

1389
01:22:32,890 --> 01:22:34,790
只是个阿肯色州来的亡命者
She is a runaway from Arkansas!

1390
01:22:34,790 --> 01:22:36,540
非常好
That is all very well.

1391
01:22:36,790 --> 01:22:38,940
你建议我把她杀了吗
Do you advise that I kill her?

1392
01:22:41,730 --> 01:22:43,550
随你的便  奈德
Do what you think is best, Ned.

1393
01:22:43,550 --> 01:22:46,270
她只不过是个迷路的小孩
She's nothing to me but a lost child.

1394
01:22:49,380 --> 01:22:50,680
先好好想想
Think it over first.

1395
01:22:50,680 --> 01:22:52,620
我已经好好想过了
I have already thought it over!

1396
01:22:52,800 --> 01:22:55,060
这样你会过来得更快
You get mounted double fast!

1397
01:22:55,060 --> 01:22:58,480
如果看到你越过那座秃山  向西北去
If I see you riding over that bald ridge to the northwest,

1398
01:22:58,480 --> 01:22:59,910
我就放了这姑娘
I will spare the girl.

1399
01:23:00,620 --> 01:23:02,150
给你五分钟
You have five minutes!

1400
01:23:02,150 --> 01:23:04,930
马上就会有一队法警过来  奈德
There will be a party of marshals here soon, Ned!

1401
01:23:04,930 --> 01:23:06,520
把这姑娘和切尼交给我
Let me have the girl and Chaney

1402
01:23:06,520 --> 01:23:09,500
我就把他们引开六个小时
and I will mislead them for six hours!

1403
01:23:09,500 --> 01:23:11,240
太不够意思了  大公鸡
Too thin, Rooster!

1404
01:23:11,240 --> 01:23:12,290
太不够意思
Too thin!

1405
01:23:12,990 --> 01:23:14,720
五分钟已经快到了
Your five minutes is running!

1406
01:23:14,720 --> 01:23:16,310
别再说了
No more talk!

1407
01:23:19,790 --> 01:23:21,230
到那山上去
Get on up that hill.

1408
01:23:23,530 --> 01:23:25,230
安静
Quiet there!

1409
01:23:32,660 --> 01:23:34,950
法雷尔  看看汤姆的伤口
Farrel, see to Tom's wound.

1410
01:23:35,320 --> 01:23:36,950
我能来点培根吗
Can I have some of that bacon?

1411
01:23:36,950 --> 01:23:38,040
随便你
You help yourself.

1412
01:23:38,550 --> 01:23:39,910
再来点咖啡
Have some of the coffee.

1413
01:23:39,910 --> 01:23:42,130
我不喝咖啡  我才十四岁
I do not drink coffee, I am fourteen.

1414
01:23:42,830 --> 01:23:46,010
我们可没有酸奶  也没有面包
Well we do not have buttermilk, and we do not have bread.

1415
01:23:46,410 --> 01:23:47,880
我们补给不足
We are poorly supplied.

1416
01:23:47,880 --> 01:23:49,710
-她在哪儿  -你在这里干嘛
- Where she is. - What are you doing here?

1417
01:23:49,710 --> 01:23:51,460
我要拧断你的小细脖子
I will ring your scrawny neck.

1418
01:23:51,470 --> 01:23:52,540
别提这茬了
You let that go.

1419
01:23:54,770 --> 01:23:56,130
怎么回事
What happened, huh?

1420
01:23:56,140 --> 01:23:58,500
我告诉你  你就会明白我占理了
I will tell you and you will see that I'm in the right.

1421
01:23:58,500 --> 01:24:00,660
汤姆・切尼在史密斯堡枪杀了我爸爸
Tom Chaney there shot my father to death in Fort Smith

1422
01:24:00,660 --> 01:24:01,740
还抢了他两个金币
and robbed him of two gold pieces

1423
01:24:01,740 --> 01:24:03,570
偷了他的牝马
and stole his mare.

1424
01:24:03,690 --> 01:24:04,890
我听说考伯恩先生很有种
I was informed Rooster Cogburn had grit

1425
01:24:04,890 --> 01:24:06,880
就雇他来抓捕凶手
and I hired him out to find the murderer.

1426
01:24:07,150 --> 01:24:09,930
刚才我正好看到切尼在饮马
A few minutes ago I came upon Chaney watering the horses.

1427
01:24:09,940 --> 01:24:11,890
他不服法  我便朝他开枪了
He would not be taken in charge and I shot him.

1428
01:24:12,720 --> 01:24:14,400
如果我把他打死
If I had killed him

1429
01:24:14,400 --> 01:24:17,200
现在就不会被抓住  可我的枪哑火了
I would not be now in this fix. My revolver misfired.

1430
01:24:17,280 --> 01:24:18,320
是这样
They will do it.

1431
01:24:18,900 --> 01:24:20,640
哑火总是会让你陷入窘境
It will embarrass you every time.

1432
01:24:21,360 --> 01:24:24,570
姑娘们都玩娃娃  可你喜欢枪  是吗
Most girls like to play pretties, but you like guns, do ya?

1433
01:24:24,570 --> 01:24:26,400
我对枪一点兴趣都没有
I do not care a thing in the world about guns.

1434
01:24:26,400 --> 01:24:27,910
如果有的话  我就会有支好使的枪了
If I did I would have one that worked.

1435
01:24:27,910 --> 01:24:29,840
我中了埋伏  奈德
I was shot from ambush, Ned.

1436
01:24:29,840 --> 01:24:31,490
马在打响鼻  不断发出噪音
The horses was blowing and making noise.

1437
01:24:31,490 --> 01:24:32,800
是警官打中我的
It was that officer that got me.

1438
01:24:32,810 --> 01:24:34,940
你怎么还能在那大言不惭
How can you sit there and tell such a big story?

1439
01:24:34,940 --> 01:24:37,690
那个坑有一百英尺深  我要把你扔进去
That pit is a hundred feet deep, and I will throw you in it.

1440
01:24:37,690 --> 01:24:39,940
让你尖叫着腐烂
I'll leave you screaming in rot.

1441
01:24:39,940 --> 01:24:41,810
-现在你觉得怎么样  -你不会的
- Now how do you like that? - No you won't.

1442
01:24:41,810 --> 01:24:43,110
这个人不会让你为所欲为的
This man will not let you have your way.

1443
01:24:43,110 --> 01:24:44,730
他是你老板  你得照他说的做
He's your boss and you have to do as he tells you.

1444
01:24:45,920 --> 01:24:47,610
我从来都没法为所欲为
Ain't nothing going my way.

1445
01:24:48,410 --> 01:24:50,740
前天晚上埋伏我们的人是大公鸡吗
Was that Rooster waylaid us night before last?

1446
01:24:50,740 --> 01:24:52,440
是考伯恩警官和我
It was Marshal Cogburn and myself.

1447
01:24:52,820 --> 01:24:54,100
你和考伯恩
You and Cogburn.

1448
01:24:55,030 --> 01:24:56,320
真厉害
Quite the posse.

1449
01:25:14,770 --> 01:25:16,070
咱们走吧  奈德
Let us move, Ned.

1450
01:25:16,070 --> 01:25:17,400
时机到了再走  医生
In good time, Doctor.

1451
01:25:17,860 --> 01:25:19,440
昆西和那孩子怎么样了
What happened to Quincy and the kid?

1452
01:25:21,950 --> 01:25:22,990
他们都死了
They are both dead.

1453
01:25:24,630 --> 01:25:27,050
我当时身历其境  太可怕了
I was in the very middle of it. It was a terrible thing to see.

1454
01:25:27,130 --> 01:25:28,980
拜托  我们走吧  奈德
Please, let us move, Ned.

1455
01:25:28,990 --> 01:25:30,520
法警已经走了
The Marshal's gone.

1456
01:25:30,520 --> 01:25:31,820
你需要好的律师吗
Do you need a good lawyer?

1457
01:25:32,350 --> 01:25:33,900
我需要好的法官
I need a good judge.

1458
01:25:34,880 --> 01:25:36,470
憧伞ずＫ乖趺囱了
What happened to Coke Hayes,

1459
01:25:36,470 --> 01:25:38,080
这老家伙被从马上射下来了
the old fellow shot off his horse.

1460
01:25:38,450 --> 01:25:39,820
也死了
Dead as well.

1461
01:25:40,610 --> 01:25:42,470
这些暴行已经结束了
These depredations have come to an end.

1462
01:25:43,140 --> 01:25:45,980
你朋友大公鸡活捉不了几个人
Your friend Rooster does not collect many prisoners.

1463
01:25:45,980 --> 01:25:47,210
他不是我的朋友
He is not my friend.

1464
01:25:49,410 --> 01:25:51,760
他把我扔给了一群野蛮人
He has abandoned me to a congress of louts.

1465
01:25:52,020 --> 01:25:53,990
你从不掩饰你的想法吗
You do not varnish your opinions.

1466
01:25:54,860 --> 01:25:56,040
我们出发吗
Are we off?

1467
01:25:56,040 --> 01:25:58,580
咱们把飞之凯蒂那票赚的分了吧
Let us cut up the winnings from the Katie Flyer.

1468
01:25:58,580 --> 01:26:00,410
到老地方再分也来得及
They'll be time for that at the old place.

1469
01:26:00,690 --> 01:26:01,960
我骑那匹灰的
I will mount the grey.

1470
01:26:01,960 --> 01:26:03,210
你有别的任务
I have other plans for you.

1471
01:26:03,210 --> 01:26:05,330
我得和医生骑一匹马吗
Must I double-mount with the Doctor?

1472
01:26:05,330 --> 01:26:06,650
-不  -不
- No! - Nope.

1473
01:26:06,660 --> 01:26:08,970
逃跑的话  两人骑一匹马太冒险了
Too chancy with two men up if it comes to a race.

1474
01:26:09,190 --> 01:26:10,920
汤姆  你和这姑娘待在这儿
Tom, you wait here with the girl.

1475
01:26:11,040 --> 01:26:12,890
到老马家后我会派卡罗尔
When we reach Ma's house I will send Carroll back

1476
01:26:12,900 --> 01:26:14,250
带新马回来
with a fresh mount.

1477
01:26:14,250 --> 01:26:15,620
你天黑出发
You will be out by dark

1478
01:26:16,250 --> 01:26:17,490
我们在老地方见
and we'll meet you at The Old Place.

1479
01:26:17,490 --> 01:26:19,100
我不想这样
I do not like that.

1480
01:26:19,200 --> 01:26:22,440
让我和你一起走  奈德  离开这再说
Let me ride with you, Ned. Just out here anyway.

1481
01:26:22,440 --> 01:26:23,640
缺一匹马
I was short a horse.

1482
01:26:23,640 --> 01:26:25,310
这里会来大批法警的
Marshals will come swarming.

1483
01:26:25,310 --> 01:26:26,900
得有段时间呢  如果他们真来的话
Hours, if they come here at all.

1484
01:26:27,020 --> 01:26:28,530
他们会以为我们都走了
They'll think that we've all gone.

1485
01:26:28,530 --> 01:26:31,040
我不要一个人和汤姆・切尼在一起
I am not staying here by myself with Tom Chaney.

1486
01:26:31,260 --> 01:26:32,510
就这么定了
That's the way I will have it.

1487
01:26:32,510 --> 01:26:33,630
他会杀了我的
He will kill me.

1488
01:26:33,640 --> 01:26:35,600
你听见他说了  他已经杀了我爸爸
You heard him say it. He's killed my father,

1489
01:26:35,600 --> 01:26:37,080
现在你还要让他杀了我
and now you will let him kill me.

1490
01:26:37,300 --> 01:26:38,790
他不会这么干的
He will do no such thing.

1491
01:26:38,940 --> 01:26:41,830
汤姆  你知道柏林路口吧
Tom, you know the crossing at Cypress Forks,

1492
01:26:41,830 --> 01:26:43,540
圆木礼拜堂附近那个
near the log meetinghouse?

1493
01:26:43,850 --> 01:26:46,280
到那儿的时候  你把这姑娘留下
When you mount it, you take the girl and leave her there.

1494
01:26:46,550 --> 01:26:47,850
明白了吗  汤姆
You understand, Tom?

1495
01:26:48,040 --> 01:26:50,470
你敢动这小妹妹一根皮毛
Any harm comes to that child,

1496
01:26:50,970 --> 01:26:52,100
你就拿不到钱
you do not get paid.

1497
01:26:54,770 --> 01:26:57,400
哈罗德  让我和你骑一匹吧
Harold, let me ride up with you.

1498
01:26:58,320 --> 01:27:01,670
哈罗德  我从我那份里付五十块钱给你
Harold, I will pay you fifty dollars out of my winnings!

1499
01:27:01,680 --> 01:27:03,150
我不重的
I am not heavy.

1500
01:27:03,480 --> 01:27:05,270
再学个牛叫  哈罗德
Do the calf again, Harold.

1501
01:27:33,280 --> 01:27:34,820
事事都跟我作对
Everything is against me.

1502
01:27:35,600 --> 01:27:37,160
你没理由抱怨
You have no reason to whine.

1503
01:27:38,180 --> 01:27:39,800
你按强盗头子的话做
If you act as the bandit chief instructed,

1504
01:27:39,800 --> 01:27:42,460
不伤害我  就能在老地方拿到报酬
and no harm comes to me, you will get your winnings at The Old Place.

1505
01:27:42,750 --> 01:27:43,880
狗屎运奈德扔下我一个人
Lucky Ned has left me,

1506
01:27:43,880 --> 01:27:46,550
他知道我只能步行的话肯定会被抓的
knowing I am sure to be caught when I leave on foot.

1507
01:27:47,390 --> 01:27:50,250
得考虑怎么逃出生天了
Must think over my position and how I may improve it.

1508
01:27:50,720 --> 01:27:53,040
另一个加州金币在哪儿
Where's the second California gold piece?

1509
01:27:55,770 --> 01:27:57,120
你把爸爸的马怎么样了
What have you done with Papa's mare?

1510
01:27:57,120 --> 01:27:58,410
安静
Keep still.

1511
01:27:59,120 --> 01:28:00,910
你是在猜测老地方在哪儿吗
Are you thinking about the old place?

1512
01:28:01,320 --> 01:28:03,370
听着  如果你放了我
Look here, if you let me go

1513
01:28:03,370 --> 01:28:04,790
我就写书面证词
I will swear to an affidavit

1514
01:28:04,790 --> 01:28:08,730
你上法庭的时候会有利于你
and once you are brought to justice, it may go easier on you.

1515
01:28:10,160 --> 01:28:12,200
告诉你  我能做得更好
I tell you I can do better than that.

1516
01:28:18,570 --> 01:28:20,690
我不需要书面证词
I need no affidavit.

1517
01:28:26,360 --> 01:28:28,260
我只需要你闭嘴
All I need is your silence.

1518
01:28:33,110 --> 01:28:35,550
你爸和你一样爱管闲事
Your father was a busybody like you.

1519
01:28:35,550 --> 01:28:38,060
说实话  我不后悔杀了他
In honesty, I do not regret shooting him.

1520
01:28:38,360 --> 01:28:40,330
他看不起汤姆・切尼
He thought Tom Chaney was small.

1521
01:28:40,660 --> 01:28:42,090
嘲笑我
Humor me.

1522
01:28:42,090 --> 01:28:44,040
你还要给我提供书面证词
And you would give me an affidavit.

1523
01:28:44,040 --> 01:28:45,990
你们都和我对着干  所有人
You're all against me! Everybody....

1524
01:28:51,960 --> 01:28:53,690
这就是切尔姆斯福特
So that is Chelmsford.

1525
01:28:55,240 --> 01:28:57,630
终于离他这么近了  有点奇怪
Strange to be so close to him at last.

1526
01:28:58,020 --> 01:29:00,800
勒波义夫先生  你怎么会在这
Mr. LeBoeuf, how is it that you are here?

1527
01:29:01,420 --> 01:29:02,610
我听到枪声
I heard the shot,

1528
01:29:02,780 --> 01:29:04,350
到了河边
and went down to the river.

1529
01:29:04,990 --> 01:29:06,860
考伯恩订了个计划
Cogburn outlined a plan.

1530
01:29:07,510 --> 01:29:09,300
注意脚下  那有个坑
Mind your footing, there's a pit there.

1531
01:29:10,060 --> 01:29:11,250
计划里面他的那部分
His part,

1532
01:29:11,740 --> 01:29:13,360
我觉得有点鲁莽
I fear is rash.

1533
01:29:15,740 --> 01:29:17,850
他回来抓捕狗屎运奈德
He returns for Lucky Ned.

1534
01:29:35,020 --> 01:29:36,270
大公鸡
Yo, Rooster!

1535
01:29:36,800 --> 01:29:38,690
你会让我们过去吗
Will you give us the road?

1536
01:29:39,790 --> 01:29:41,440
一对四  太莽撞了
One against four. It is ill advised.

1537
01:29:41,950 --> 01:29:43,670
他不听劝的
He would not be dissuaded.

1538
01:29:43,670 --> 01:29:46,540
奈德  有几个人和那姑娘在一起
Hello, Ned. How many men are with the girl?

1539
01:29:47,090 --> 01:29:48,450
只有切尼
Just Chaney.

1540
01:29:48,450 --> 01:29:50,200
我们的协议已经执行了
Our agreement is in force.

1541
01:29:50,550 --> 01:29:53,560
上次我看见她时  她还好得很呢
She was in excellent health, when last I saw her.

1542
01:29:54,460 --> 01:29:58,410
法雷尔  我希望你和你兄弟都置身事外
Farrel, I want you and your brother to stand clear.

1543
01:29:59,260 --> 01:30:00,780
你也一样  医生
You as well, Doctor.

1544
01:30:01,080 --> 01:30:03,270
今天对你们没兴趣
I have no interest in you today.

1545
01:30:04,410 --> 01:30:06,300
你想干什么  大公鸡
What is your intention, Rooster?

1546
01:30:06,670 --> 01:30:08,920
你以为一对四能算旗鼓相当吗
Do you think one on four is a dogfall?

1547
01:30:09,480 --> 01:30:12,170
我要在一分钟之内要你命  奈德
I mean to kill you in one minute, Ned.

1548
01:30:12,770 --> 01:30:14,810
或者在帕克法官有空的时候
Or see you hanged at Fort Smith

1549
01:30:14,810 --> 01:30:16,720
把你吊死在史密斯堡
at Judge Parker's convenience.

1550
01:30:17,510 --> 01:30:18,980
你选哪种
Which will you have?

1551
01:30:19,910 --> 01:30:21,990
你这是独眼肥猪的
I call that, bold talk

1552
01:30:22,180 --> 01:30:23,860
痴心妄想
for a one-eyed fat man!

1553
01:30:28,510 --> 01:30:31,170
把枪拿好  你个狗娘养的
Fill your hand, you son of a bitch!

1554
01:30:46,320 --> 01:30:47,640
开枪啊  勒波义夫先生
Shoot them, Mr. LeBoeuf!

1555
01:30:47,650 --> 01:30:49,920
他们太远了  移动太快
To far, moving to fast.

